A quick tip for beginners that don't have a belt sander (like me) - you don't really need one. It's a great tool that's worth getting, but if you have a bench grinder (the one with grinding wheels) or even grinding attachments to your angle grinder, it also works great. Of course, for angle grinder you also need a vise, vise grips or C-clamps to secure the piece. Also also - you'd be surprised, how much material can a simple file remove.

Also - if you're just starting out, you don't really need to harden and quench it, it will just hold the edge for shorter and could be prone to bending.
